results.name: a(n) = the largest k < n for which A277892(k) = A277892(n), 0 if no such number exists, a(0) = a(1) = 0.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000 (computed from the 10000 term b-file provided by _Hans Havermann_ for A277892)
program: (Scheme) (define (A277894 n) (cond ((<= n 2) 0) (else (let ((v (A277892 n))) (let loop ((k (- n 1))) (cond ((= 1 k) 0) ((= (A277892 k) v) k) (else (loop (- k 1)))))))))
